The paper proposes a new neural network architecture for sequence modelling, which is a popular topic in machine learning and falls under the category of deep learning. The paper specifically focuses on modelling long term temporal dependencies, which is a sub-topic of sequence modelling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the proposed network is applied to trajectory prediction problems. Additionally, the paper also mentions part-of-speech tagging, which falls under the sub-category of natural language processing (NLP), hence cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper applies the proposed network to a surveillance setting, which falls under the sub-category of robotics, hence cs.RO (Robotics) is also a possible sub-category.
